      <h2>Program Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        This program introduces machine learning techniques for seismic data processing,
        with emphasis on both practical implementation and research-oriented applications.
        The course addresses modern challenges in noise attenuation, imaging, and interpretation
        of seismic data.
      </p>

      <h2>Program Scope</h2>
      <p>
        The training bridges classical seismic processing workflows and modern data-driven
        methodologies, including deep learning and hybrid physics-informed approaches.
        Participants gain insight into how machine learning complements physical modeling
        rather than replacing it.
      </p>

      <h2>Program Topics</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Machine learning fundamentals for geosciences</li>
        <li>Seismic denoising, interpolation, and enhancement</li>
        <li>Deep learning architectures for seismic data</li>
        <li>Physics-informed and hybrid learning models</li>
        <li>Case studies from research and industry</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Courses / Teaching Materials</h2>
      <p>
        Teaching materials are organized to progressively introduce machine learning concepts
        and demonstrate their application to real seismic datasets. The focus is on reproducible
        workflows, interpretability, and physical consistency.
      </p>

      <p>
        Course resources include lecture notes, slides, and hands-on exercises based on
        realistic seismic processing problems encountered in academic and industrial research.
      </p>

